rComments: Women's music. She is a little boring, reading is definitely boring, but I like her. Some of her lectures can be interesting. I love the background stuff on music and what not.

Her class was horrible. It was boring and when she goes through the slides, she goes through it hella fast. Her two papers seem easy but not really. Taking notes in class might not help. don't take this class!!!!

She is so passionate and really knows the material. No section and plenty of reading. If you can push through the first half of the quarter, past the classical and experimental, you'll do wonderfully. Two easy as pie papers and your usual midterm/final with listening questions. DO THE LISTENING AND THE READING!!! Lecture was mandatory... :(

Yara is a slightly boring lecturer who uses powerpoint and music clips effectively, if you go see her during office hours she is very helpful. Lots of reading, if you go to class and pay attention you dont have to do more than skim the reading.  Great pianist and knowlege of musical terms and their application.  Tries to not bash men in a fem class
